Hardware Requirements:

1. Arduino Uno / ESP32 / NodeMCU – microcontroller board  
2. Accelerometer & Gyroscope (e.g., MPU6050) – to detect impact  
3. GPS Module (e.g., Neo-6M) – to get location coordinates  
4. GSM Module (e.g., SIM800L) – to send alerts via SMS  
5. Buzzer – to give a local alert  
6. LEDs – for visual indicators  
7. Power Supply / Battery Pack  
8. Wires, Breadboard, or PCB – for connections  
9. Optional: Camera Module – for evidence/photo capture



Software Requirements:

1. Arduino IDE – for programming microcontroller  
2. Embedded C / C++ – language for Arduino programming  
3. Cloud Platform (e.g., ThingSpeak, Blynk, Firebase) – for real-time monitoring  
4. Python (optional) – for backend logic or server communication  
5. Mobile App (optional) – for notifications  
6. APIs (e.g., Twilio / SMTP) – to send alerts or emails  



Functional Requirements:

- Detect collision using sensor data  
- Send location and alert to emergency contact  
- Display accident status via LEDs/buzzer  

